# Dev Tools Server Configuration
# This file documents all available environment variables for the dev tools server.
# 
# For local setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace paths with your machine's actual storage locations
# 3. Keep .env.local out of git (it's in .gitignore)

# ============================================================================
# Storage Paths
# ============================================================================
# Where infrastructure service data is stored on the host.
# On Windows with Docker Desktop: use forward slashes
# On macOS/Linux: use $HOME or full path
# 
# Recommendations:
# - Use dedicated directories outside project workspaces
# - Ensure adequate disk space (Ollama models can be large)
# - Back up these paths if they contain important data

OLLAMA_STORAGE_PATH=${HOME}/.ollama
SONARQUBE_STORAGE_PATH=${HOME}/.sonarqube

# ============================================================================
# Service Access (Optional Overrides)
# ============================================================================
# By default, services are accessible via Docker network names and localhost.
# Projects can override these if connecting to remote infrastructure.
# 
# Default values (no need to set unless customizing):
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://ollama:11434
# SONARQUBE_URL=http://sonarqube:9000
# DOCS_MCP_URL=http://docs-mcp:6280

# ============================================================================
# Secrets (Optional - add to .env.local if needed)
# ============================================================================
# Most infrastructure services work without these, but you can add:
# SONARQUBE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin  # Change default admin password
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=sonar         # Customize database password